<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00025</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR A COMPREHENSIVE NUCLEAR REGULATION, CREATING FOR THE PURPOSE, THE PHILIPPINE NUCLEAR REGULATORY COMMISSION, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Comprehensive Nuclear Regulation Act</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to encompass the relocation of all regulatory activities performed by the Philippine Nuclear Regulatory Institute (PNRI) under Department of Science and Technology (DOST) and those in the Bureau of Health Devices and Technology (BHDT) under Department of Health (DOH), which are specific to ionizing radiation regulation, to position within the governmental organizational structure, such as the Office of the President, that guarantees that controlling functions of a regulatory body are separate from the promoting functions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ABAYA, FRANCIS GERALD A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Mercado (080 2017-03-08)</td><td>2. Pineda (007 2017-08-07)</td><tr><td>3. Tambunting (000 2017-11-27)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Change of committee referral requested on 2017-01-30</b><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB08733</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2017-01-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION on 2016-07-26;SECONDARILY REFERRED TO ENERGY on 2016-07-26;</td></tr></table>